The authors of this driver and accompanying userland and teensy code
are listed here. Any authors should feel free to add themselves here
in whatever way they feel is appropriate.

Andrew Sackville-West <andrew@swclan.homelinux.org> -- initial
implementation of the core of the teensy driver kernel module, random
hacking throughout.

Nathan Collins <nathan.collins@gmail.com>: "submodule" architecture,
with kernel-submodules in kernel land and handler dispatch in hw land;
initial pack/unpack architecture/implementation in kernel/hw land;
skeletal adc/mc submodule implementation, including kernel land
drivers and hw land handlers; userland mc control app implementation.
